  "title": "QMS Engineer (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of Implementing and maintaining the Quality Management System standards and Environment,      Health and Safety SOPs and Manuals.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in ensuring adherence to Compliance and Regulatory Oversight for Standard Operating     Procedure, Quality and Safety Manuals, Maintenance Organisation Expositions.</li>\n  <li>In charge of Certification Audits by Civil Aviation and liaising with assigned CAA Principal Maintenance Inspector for approvals, certifications and inspections.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in conducting Internal Quality Audit, External vendor QMS audits as well as managing vendor qualification into the Approved Vendor List</li>\n  <li>Take charge of assigned audit conducted by Customer.</li>\n  <li>In-Charge of the Quality and Safety of assigned workshop</li>\n  <li>Responsible for conducting investigations for incidents and accidents, warranty</li>\n  <li>Responsible assisting the Manager in developing, reviewing, improving and implementing quality and      safety management procedures</li>\n  <li>Attend meetings and other duties as delegated by the Quality Manager</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Diploma in aerospace engineering/engineering</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years of in QMS in Aerospace Industry.</li>\n  <li>Qualified Auditor is required</li>\n</ul>",
